# Generated by Cargo
# will have compiled files and executables
/target/
# Ephemeral merged configs written by scripts/dev/tauri-dev-test.mjs (devUrl
# override for parallel instances); created at launch, removed on exit. The
# instance name is part of the filename (`devtest`, `l2full`, …), so match the
# whole family — a crashed run leaves its file behind and it must not become a
# commit candidate for the next session that happens to run `git status`.
/.tauri-*.gen.conf.json
# Alternate target dir used when the primary target/ is locked by tauri dev.
/target-bindings/
/gen/schemas
# ts-rs default output dir. We redirect to repo-root `src/lib/bindings/` via
# `build.rs` (cargo:rustc-env=TS_RS_EXPORT_DIR), but if a future ts-rs change
# or a forgotten env override writes here instead, the gitignore prevents
# the dual-tree drift from coming back. The src/lib/bindings/ tree is the
# single source of truth.
/bindings/
